 with a 5/1 mass ratio.<br>
2. This Orion has a mass of 100,000,000 kilograms.<br>
3. It has 80,000,000 kilograms of mass in its steel  <br>
Pu magizine in the form of gun type U -235 fueled<br>
  40-45 Kiloton  A-bombs. Each pulse unit has <br>
a mass of 1,000 kilograms. There are 80,000 of them.<br>
4. The Pu magizine has a mass of 16,000,000 kilograms.<br>
5.The payload has a mass of 2,000,000 kilograms.<br>
6. The Impulse absorber system has a mass of<br>
2,000,000 kilograms.It includes pusher plate, and steel pneumonic springs behind it.<br>
7.There is a 200 meter diameter steel pusher plate.<br>
8. Pu detonation occurrs at point 0 which is 200 meters behind orion.<br>
9. The pu ejector throws the pus out at 10 m/sec.<br>
10. Pu detonation occurrs 20 seconds after ejection.<br>
11.The atomic fireball of the Pu s is about 200 meters in diameter at full expansion.<br>
12.This allows a 50% debris collimation when the pu s<br>
 blow up.<br>
13. The pu s have a 2 inch thick casing made of lead metal<br>
around them.<br>
14. The pulse units  contain a 1 meter long, and 8 inch wide<br>
 steel gun barrel in the center. They have a cylindrical shape.<br>
15.One end of the barrell is closed by a steel plate.<br>
This end of the barrel has a 30 kilogram 100% pure hemisphere<br>
of solid Uranium 235 metal, that is wielded inside of <br>
of 1 inch thich hollow hemisphere of berylium metal.<br>
16. The other end of the barrel has a steel cartidrige<br>
screwed into it.The other  end of the gun barrel is threaded so  that the cartidge can be screwed in it .<br>
17. The cartidge has A 30 kilogram solid  hemisphere of<br>
 100 % Heu in it.<br>
17. This is wielded inside of 1 inch thich Berylium metal<br>
hemisphere.<br>
18. The cartride contains a 1.5 kilogram charge of cordite behind the U 235 bullet. There is a thin layer of mercury fulminite in the back end of the cartridge behind the cordite.<br>
19.The gun barrel assembly is inside of a steel capsule.<br>
20.The U 235  cartidge has an electric detonator attached to its center. This is detonated by a radio remote controled solenoid switch.<br>
 21. To fire the pu, the radio signal is transmitted, and closes<br>
the solenoid switch. This completes electric circuit, and fires the detonator. The detonator detonates the mercury fulminite<br>
which detonates the cordite. The 30 Kilogram U 235 hemisphere is fired into the other U 235 hemisphere to make<br>
 a common ball of supercritical mass. This results in the atomic blast of the pu. Using berylium tamper the critical<br>
mass is 20 kg. 60/3 = 3 critical masses. By atomic scaling <br>
rules this will generate about a 45 kiloton atomic explosion.<br>
22.The debris is thrown at the pusher plate at about <br>
2000 kilometers a second in velocity. Half of it hits the <br>
pusher plate at this velocity.  This transfers 2,000,000<br>
* 5000 kilograms of impulse to Orion.This is 10,000,000,000<br>
kilograms of momentum force.<br>
10,000,000,000/100,000,000 = 100 meters a second.<br>
Each pu boost orion by 10 Gs which is 100 m/sec.<br>
23. The springs absorb this force, store it and then release it<br>
 slowly to accelerate orion via the recoil.<br>
24. By the rcocket eqaution this orion can reach a delta v of<br>
1,000,000 * ln 5/1 if it uses all the pus. This is 1,600,000<br>
meters a sec, which is about 3,200,000 miles per hour.<br>
